2
00:00:48,720 --> 00:00:49,720
You're …

3
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:52,720
Her mother?

4
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:57,000
We're old friends who haven't seen each other for years.

5
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Shouldn't you first ask me how I've been all this time?

6
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:04,479
If you're just going to be snarky, then I'm leaving.

7
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:07,720
Please don't be mad.

8
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:14,000
The world is too small.

9
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:17,000
What's the chances that you and Anueng know each other?

10
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:23,480
Do you want to know what I named my daughter Anueng?

11
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:27,000
You wanted her name to be similar to mine?

12
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:31,000
You were smart when we were friends in school.

13
00:01:31,720 --> 00:01:33,480
And you're still smart today.

14
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,240
But why?

15
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:38,720
Why did you give her a name similar to mine?

16
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:44,000
To be a constant reminder of the damage you caused.

17
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:48,240
What's it got to do with me?

18
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:54,000
Do I need to remind you?

19
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:07,000
What do you mean you like me?

20
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:09,000
We are just friends.

21
00:02:09,479 --> 00:02:11,239
Why can't I like you?

22
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:13,480
Nueng … you know me.

23
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:17,720
No one can ever love you as much as I love you.

24
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:20,239
But I don't love you.

25
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:22,480
Why would you confess to me?

26
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:24,720
I just wanted you to know.

27
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:28,480
I didn't want to keep it a secret from you any longer.

28
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:30,000
Now its awkward.

29
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,240
How can things now be the same between us?

30
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Well, I've told you now.

31
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:39,000
So … do you have anything to say?

32
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:43,000
I've already told you, I don't like you like that.

33
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,000
What do you want me to say?

34
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:49,720
I love you and I want you to only see me.

35
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:52,239
I can see you now.

36
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:55,000
You know what I mean.

37
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:57,239
Don't pretend you don't understand.

38
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,720
What do you want me to say?

39
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:02,480
Listen.

40
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:05,000
I've already told you,

41
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,720
I will never be involved with you.

42
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:10,239
Why not Nueng?

43
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:13,240
You don't need to know.

44
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:15,480
Tell me why.

45
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:19,000
You're not worthy of me.

46
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:21,480
We're from different social classes.

47
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,480
Here … take this.

48
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,240
You're only 16. You shouldn't be pregnant.

49
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:40,000
But … Nueng.

50
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,240
I don't want this.

51
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:44,240
The baby didn't do anything wrong.

52
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:46,000
Are you really ready to be a mother?

53
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:48,720
Will the guy take responsibility as well?

54
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:53,720
Don't let this pregnancy ruin your life.

55
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:58,000
The most important thing is your future.

56
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:00,000
Not that baby.

57
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:03,480
Nueng.

58
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,480
Remember now? Everything you did?

59
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:17,480
Anueng almost wasn't born because of you.

60
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:23,000
I never thought I'd see you so shocked.

61
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:26,240
I'm honoured to have witnessed this.

62
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,720
You drank that mixture?

63
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,480
I did.

64
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:43,000
Oh … you look like you've seen a ghost.

65
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:51,480
After I drank it, I was afraid and ran and told my mother.

66
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:54,480
We were able to save Anueng.

67
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,480
I'm glad.

68
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,480
You're glad?

69
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:12,240
Anueng was born prematurely and was in an incubator for months.

70
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:18,480
She needs to wear thick glasses because eyesight is so poor.

71
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,720
She had to start school three years late.

72
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,000
All this happened because I nearly miscarried.

73
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:39,480
I was wondering, why you need such thick glasses.

74
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:45,480
Well, I already told you that my mother tried to get rid of me.

75
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:47,000
It caused me to be born prematurely.

76
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,480
This caused my eyesight to be poor.

77
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,000
I feel deeply hurt.

78
00:05:57,240 --> 00:06:03,000
Because I believed and trusted my close friend - Nueng.

79
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,480
So I named my daughter Anueng.

80
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:11,480
So people would give her the nickname 'Nueng.

81
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:16,480
So I would never forget the person who hurt me the most.

82
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:22,240
The person who said Anueng should never be born.

83
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Who would have guessed,

84
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,000
That the Universe would conspire,

85
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:38,000
To bring Anueng to meet the person who didn't want her born.

86
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,000
Is this fate?

87
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Nueng.

88
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:02,000
Where's Piengfah?

89
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:08,000
She's back there.

90
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:12,240
What did you talk about. You look upset.

91
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:20,720
We talked about your relationship with her when she was in high school.

92
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,000
Congratulations

93
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,480
You have a daughter.

94
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:34,000
I need to go.

95
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:49,000
Miss Nueng, are you leaving?

96
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,480
Yes

97
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,480
Why are you in a hurry to leave?

98
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,000
I'm tired.

99
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:02,480
Aww … if you don't stay, then I don't want to stay either.

100
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:08,000
Please stay a little longer … so you can keep me company.

101
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:12,000
If you're here, then I've got someone by my side.

102
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:25,000
Why are you crying? Who made you cry?

103
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,000
Nobody.

104
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:44,000
I'm here for you. Please don't cry.

105
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:53,000
Miss Nueng.

106
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:13,240
Thank you for being alive.

107
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,000
Huh?

108
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:27,480
Thank you for being born.

109
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,000
My good girl.

110
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:22,000
(sigh)

111
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:43,480
You haven't said a word, or eaten anything since I arrived.

112
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:47,720
I'm not hungry.

113
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:51,000
Is Anueng really my daughter?

114
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,000
How old is Anueng now?

115
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,000
20.

116
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:11,000
She's the right age to be Piengfah's and my daughter.

117
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:15,240
Back then, did you know Piengfah was pregnant?

118
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:25,000
I was too young and immature to be a father.

119
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:28,000
I didn't know what to do.

120
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:33,000
What about Piengfah?

121
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:37,480
She told me and then completely disappeared.

122
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:43,000
Back then … I was just very immature.

123
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,000
I guess I'm a bad guy.

124
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:53,000
Should I get a DNA test?

125
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:58,000
I'm not asking because I want to avoid responsibility.

126
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:00,480
I want to be certain.

127
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,000
Because now I am ready to take responsibility.

128
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:08,720
Then you should get a DNA test.

129
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:11,000
But 'Nueng might not appreciate it.

130
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,000
I mean, Anueng.

131
00:13:17,240 --> 00:13:18,480
Nervous?

132
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:22,000
I didn't know you wanted a child.

133
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:28,480
As I told you, I'm ready now to take responsibility.

134
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:31,480
Now that I know she exists.

135
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:36,000
And … my daughter is very cute.

136
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,240
I agree.

137
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,000
Anueng is very cute.

138
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:46,720
It would have been horrible if Piengfah didn't get to the hospital in time.

139
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:51,480
But she did make it in time … and my daughter is very strong.

140
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:59,480
Listen to you … you keep saying "daughter", "daughter"

141
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,480
You're so excited.

142
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,480
As soon as I found out she was my daughter,

143
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:09,000
I loved her immediately.

144
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:11,000
It's strange.

145
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,480
Even though I didn't raise her,

146
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,720
I still love her so much.

147
00:14:16,379 --> 00:14:18,000
It's not strange at all.

148
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:20,480
Anueng is easy to love.

149
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:25,000
Whoever is close to her will naturally fall in love with her.

150
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,480
Do you also feel that way?

151
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:31,480
I'm not in love … I'm just saying she's adorable.

152
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:34,480
I've never seen you care for anyone,

153
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:38,000
But you really seem to care about Anueng.

154
00:14:39,372 --> 00:14:42,719
She is lucky to have you by her side.

155
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:45,000
Be quiet.

156
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:15,000
Miss Nueng.

157
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:24,000
Hello Mr Chet.

158
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,480
Are you well?

159
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:28,000
I'm fine, thank you.

160
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,720
Did you have lots of fun at school?

161
00:15:36,010 --> 00:15:38,000
Yes … fun.

162
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:45,000
You should go home. I'll call you later.

163
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:47,000
But I …

164
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:49,286
Have lots of fun on your way home.

165
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,000
Huh?

166
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:55,000
That's a weird way to say it.

167
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:57,920
I just said the same thing you did.

168
00:15:58,480 --> 00:16:02,000
But you understood what I said, so please head home.

169
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:09,240
OK

170
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,000
He looked confused.

171
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:40,480
He probably needs more sleep.

172
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,480
Why did you wait for me?

173
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:45,480
No reason.

174
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:50,480
No reason? Then why are you here?

175
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:55,480
Why do I need a reason to see you?

176
00:16:57,035 --> 00:16:58,480
I just missed you.

177
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,000
What's the matter?

178
00:17:09,480 --> 00:17:11,000
Nothing.

179
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:18,000
I haven't seen you since the school's centenary event.

180
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:23,000
How are you here now?

181
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:26,000
Did your grandma allow you to meet me?

182
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,000
How did you know?

183
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:36,000
Since that event, grandma will let me meet with you.

184
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:40,000
She said I could invite you over for a meal.

185
00:17:40,607 --> 00:17:43,600
It's because you are descended from royalty.

186
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,000
Invite me to have a meal?

187
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:54,240
I'll go if I'm not busy.

188
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:02,000
You're acting strange today.

189
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:06,000
No I'm not.

190
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:09,480
Why are you avoiding eye contact?

191
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:12,240
Are you feeling guilty about something?

192
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:13,720
No.

193
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,240
You're still avoiding eye contact.

194
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:18,480
No I'm not.

195
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:21,240
You did it again. You looked away.

196
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:25,480
The confident Miss Nueng never acted like this.

197
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:29,240
You've definitely done something wrong.

198
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:32,240
Is that why my mother wants to talk to you?

199
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:37,240
Did my mother say something to you?

200
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:40,480
She did, otherwise you wouldn't acting like this.

201
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:03,480
What's the matter? Are you mad with me?

202
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:05,480
I'm not.

203
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:08,480
If you're not mad, then why are you like this?

204
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,480
Don't pester me. I'm not mad at you.

205
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:15,240
If your not mad, then do you hate me?

206
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:18,480
Wow … why are you so mean?

207
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:21,000
Don't be silly. I don't hate you.

208
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,240
If not hate then must be love.

209
00:19:22,240 --> 00:19:23,500
Yes.

210
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,720
What was that?

211
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:40,480
Just now, you said "yes".

212
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:45,000
So what?

213
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:48,000
It means that you do love me.

214
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:50,720
I want to know what type of love?

215
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:52,240
or …

216
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:53,480
You should go home.

217
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:55,240
You always chase me away.

218
00:19:55,240 --> 00:19:57,240
I don't want to go home yet.

219
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:01,720
If you're late, your grandma will yell at you. 

220
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:04,000
Grandma won't yell at me,

221
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:08,240
She focussed on my mother now that she's back from overseas.

222
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:11,480
You should go home and spend time with your mother.

223
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,240
I don't want to.

224
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,000
Why not?

225
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:19,000
I hate my mother.

226
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:27,240
My mother said that you were the reason I almost wasn't born.

227
00:20:33,019 --> 00:20:35,000
Did she think I'd believe her?

228
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:37,720
My mother didn't want me.

229
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:41,000
She should blame herself.

230
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,000
Why would she lie about this?

231
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:51,480
Don't worry. I don't believe anything my mother says.

232
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:56,480
I won't stop loving you because of what she said.

233
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:04,480
Did you say that to your mother?

234
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:12,480
Of course not … I only said that to you.

235
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:19,000
Why? Are you afraid of losing me?

236
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,480
You're not funny.

237
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:29,240
Aww … you're so mean.

238
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:33,000
But when you are mean … I like it.

239
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:44,000
But I'm not OK with my mother blaming you.

240
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:52,480
Anueng.

241
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:56,480
I ...

242
00:22:06,480 --> 00:22:07,720
It's my mother.

243
00:22:44,240 --> 00:22:47,000
Anueng. Grandma is waiting for you.

244
00:22:47,759 --> 00:22:48,240
But …

245
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:49,480
Go inside.

246
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:03,480
Why did you tell Anueng it was my fault she almost wasn't born?

247
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:06,000
Because … its true.

248
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:09,480
My daughter prefers you over me.

249
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:13,240
Even though you nearly caused her death.

250
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:18,000
But now I'm so relieved that she's alive.

251
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:22,720
I'm deeply ashamed … about what I did back then.

252
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:28,240
I understand why you hate me for what I did.

253
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:31,000
But why drag Anueng into this mess?

254
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:33,000
You ask why?

255
00:23:33,720 --> 00:23:37,000
Anueng knows that it was you who almost caused her death.

256
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:40,480
Does it even bother you at all?

257
00:23:44,480 --> 00:23:48,240
You wanted to talk to me … just to ask me that?

258
00:23:50,480 --> 00:23:51,720
Well I'll answer.

259
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:55,240
I'm consumed with guilt,

260
00:23:55,720 --> 00:24:00,000
For the pain and hurt I caused back then.

261
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:07,480
Please help me to get closer to my daughter.

262
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:16,000
I'm not family. How am I supposed to do that?

263
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:20,480
Anueng trusts you.

264
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,480
Please?

265
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:33,720
I'm going to get married, when I get back to America.

266
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:37,000
I haven't even told my mother yet.

267
00:24:38,240 --> 00:24:40,720
I want to take Anueng back with me.

268
00:24:46,017 --> 00:24:48,017
Are you two still talking?

269
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:58,000
What are you talking about?

270
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:01,000
I was just asking Miss Nueng,

271
00:25:02,720 --> 00:25:04,480
If we should take you to the amusement park.

272
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:06,720
